                <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                  What is a vaccine and how does it work?
                  <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                  A vaccine helps your body develop immunity to a disease by mimicking an infection. It stimulates your immune system to produce antibodies.
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                  Are vaccines safe?
                  <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                  Yes, vaccines undergo rigorous testing in clinical trials and are constantly monitored for safety after approval by health authorities.
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                  Do vaccines have side effects?
                  <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                  Most side effects are minor, like a sore arm or mild fever, and go away quickly. Serious side effects are very rare.
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                  Can I still get the disease after vaccination?
                  <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                  No vaccine is 100% effective, but vaccinated people are much less likely to get sick. If they do, the illness is usually milder.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
